1. Project Overview
Title: Arpalink - A Local Service Provider

Description: Arpalink is a web application designed to facilitate local service provider registration and user profile management. Users can register with their details and view their profiles.

2. Features
User registration with validation.
Display of user profile information.
Simple and intuitive user interface.

3. Installation Instructions
Prerequisites:

Java Development Kit (JDK) 11 
Apache Maven 3.6 
An IDE (Eclipse,).


Steps to Set Up:
Clone the repository:



git clone 
cd arpalink
Build the project using Maven:


mvn clean install
Deploy the WAR file to a servlet container  Apache Tomcat.


4. Usage Instructions
Open a web browser and navigate to https://github.com/manishsahani1234/Arpalink
Fill in the registration form with a username, password, and email.
Click the "Register" button to create a new user.
After registration, the user will be redirected to their profile page, displaying their information.



5. Unit Testing
Unit tests are included for the DAO and service layers.
To run the tests, use the following command:


mvn test

